        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 7:37PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 737 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mishawaka, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
South Bend, Elkhart, Mishawaka, Goshen, Dunlap, Gulivoire Park,
Simonton Lake, Granger, Osceola, Wakarusa, Woodland, Jimtown, and
Wyatt.

This includes Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 89 and
94.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
